### 1.5 Offsets — describe and reset

**Describe** a group:

```bash
bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server 10.0.0.190:9092 \
  --group cg-vla-conversion-pipeline-de-conversion-processing --describe
```

**Reset:** the consumer group must have **no running consumers**, or the broker rejects the reset. Use **`--dry-run`** first where supported; add **`--execute`** to apply.

Common reset modes (see `kafka-consumer-groups.sh --help` for the full set):

| Option | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `--shift-by <n>` | Move offset forward/back by `n` |
| `--to-current` | Reset to current position |
| `--to-latest` | Jump to end |
| `--to-offset <n>` | Exact offset |
| `--to-datetime <string>` | e.g. `2022-11-02T00:00:00.000` |
| `--by-duration <ISO-8601>` | e.g. `PT0H30M0S` (30 minutes back from “now” at reset time) |
| `--all-topics` | Apply to every topic the group subscribes to |

Examples:

```bash
bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --group <group_name> \
  --reset-offsets --shift-by -10 --topic <topic_name> --dry-run

bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --group <group_name> \
  --reset-offsets --shift-by -10 --topic <topic_name> --execute
```

```bash
bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --group <group_name> \
  --reset-offsets --all-topics --to-datetime 2022-11-02T00:00:00.000 --dry-run
```

```bash
bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --group <group_name> \
  --reset-offsets --all-topics --by-duration PT0H30M0S --execute
```

Production-style reprocessing (appserver/data-engine stopped, validation, rollback) is in **§13**.

