## 6. Multi-broker only — add / update

| Property | Rule | Example |
|----------|------|---------|
| **`node.id`** | **Unique** on every node in the cluster; often **1 … N** | `1`, `2`, `3` |
| **`controller.quorum.voters`** | On **all** controller **and** broker nodes: `id@host:port` list | `controller.quorum.voters=1@localhost:9093,2@localhost:9095,3@localhost:9097` |
| **`offsets.topic.replication.factor`** | `N` = number of **brokers** | `offsets.topic.replication.factor=3` |
| **`transaction.state.log.replication.factor`** | Same `N` | `transaction.state.log.replication.factor=3` |
| **`transaction.state.log.min.isr`** | Often **`N-1`**; if **&lt; 3 brokers**, use **1** | `transaction.state.log.min.isr=2` (example when N=3) |
| **`listeners`** | Client + controller listeners | `listeners=PLAINTEXT://localhost:9092,CONTROLLER://localhost:9093` (replace host/port as needed) |
| **`advertised.listeners`** | What clients use | `advertised.listeners=PLAINTEXT://localhost:9092` |
| **`min.insync.replicas`** | Often **`N-1`**; if **&lt; 3 brokers**, use **1** | `min.insync.replicas=2` (example when N=3) |
| **`default.replication.factor`** | `N` brokers | `default.replication.factor=3` |

**3-node example (2 controllers + 1 broker):** set **`controller.quorum.voters`** consistently on **all three** nodes to the three `id@ip:port` entries (see Confluence diagram).

