## 12. EC2 → EKS migration (Strimzi — phased plan)

High-level phases for moving Kafka to **EKS (Strimzi)** with **observability** (JMX, Prometheus), **log shipping** (Fluent Bit dual-write), and **Logstash → OpenSearch** aligned before **producer cutover** and **decommissioning EC2**.

| Phase | Key steps |
|-------|-----------|
| **1** | List topics, consumer groups, producers; capture **`server.properties`** (baseline). |
| **2** | **EKS + Strimzi**; **Kafka** CR + **KafkaNodePool**; topics; **NLB + DNS**; connectivity tests. |
| **3** | Align broker/topic config with **EC2** behaviour; scale **replicas / resources / storage**. |
| **4** | **JMX** on **9090**; expose via **NLB** or **NodePort**; **Prometheus** scrape + alerts/dashboards. |
| **5** | **Fluent Bit:** add EKS **OUTPUT**s (dual write); approval; deploy/restart; verify **both** clusters receive logs. |
| **6** | **Logstash:** point to EKS (or dual read); fix **DNS** if needed; rollout restart; verify in **OpenSearch**. |
| **7** | **Switch producers to EKS only**; validate; **decommission EC2 Kafka**. |

**Interview hooks (one line each):** (1) Discovery — inventory + config snapshot. (2) Strimzi CRs + node pools; NLB fronts bootstrap. (3) Parity — RF, retention, ISR, capacity vs legacy. (4) JMX → Prometheus; secure exposure. (5) Dual-write de-risks until verification. (6) Logstash/OpenSearch must resolve brokers (DNS). (7) Producers last — avoid starving EC2 consumers.

*Order:* do not point Logstash or producers to EKS-only until phases 2–4 (and usually 5–6) prove stable.

