```

Also see operational write-ups (e.g. [Contactsunny — manual topic delete](https://contactsunny.medium.com/manually-delete-apache-kafka-topics-424c7e016ff3)).

### 16.9 ZK ensemble errors (`Connection refused` during leader election)

- Ensure distinct **`myid`** per ZK node (`/var/lib/zookeeper/myid` or image-specific path).
- Check **quorum** ports / firewall between ZK peers.

### 16.10 `broker-list` vs `bootstrap-servers`

- **Producer (old):** `--broker-list` — full broker list; missing brokers can break produce.
- **Consumer / modern CLI:** `--bootstrap-server` — usually **one** reachable broker is enough to discover metadata.
- **Zookeeper connection string:** `host:port` or `h1:2181,h2:2181,h3:2181/chroot` — see [Kafka docs — `zookeeper.connect`](https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/#brokerconfigs_zookeeper.connect).

### 16.11 Consumer config — timeouts (interview / tuning)

| Concept | Role |
|---------|------|
| `heartbeat.interval.ms` | Time between heartbeats to the group coordinator |
| `session.timeout.ms` | How long without heartbeat before the member is considered dead |
| `request.timeout.ms` | Client-side request timeout |
| `max.poll.interval.ms` | Max delay between `poll()` calls while processing; exceed → rebalance |

Rough rule: **process crash** often detected in ~`session.timeout.ms`; **slow processing** is bounded by **`max.poll.interval.ms`**. See [KAFKA-3806](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3806) and current broker defaults for **offset retention**.

